    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn23.14:1.1",
          "pli": "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. ",
          "en": "At Sāvatthī. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn23.14:1.2",
          "pli": "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā rādho bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: ",
          "en": "Seated to one side, Venerable Rādha said to the Buddha: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn23.14:1.3",
          "pli": "“‘aniccadhammo, aniccadhammo’ti, bhante, vuccati. ",
          "en": "“Sir, they speak of this thing called ‘naturally impermanent’. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn23.14:1.4",
          "pli": "Katamo nu kho, bhante, aniccadhammo”ti? ",
          "en": "What is naturally impermanent? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn23.14:1.5",
          "pli": "“Rūpaṃ kho, rādha, aniccadhammo, vedanā aniccadhammo, saññā aniccadhammo, saṅkhārā aniccadhammo, viññāṇaṃ aniccadhammo. ",
          "en": "“Rādha, form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness are naturally impermanent. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn23.14:1.6",
          "pli": "Evaṃ passaṃ … pe … ",
          "en": "Seeing this … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn23.14:1.7",
          "pli": "nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānātī”ti. ",
          "en": "They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn23.14:1.8",
          "pli": "Catutthaṃ. ",
          "en": ""
        }
      ],
